---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: Curious Tinkerer
personaId: tinkerer
permalink: /tinkerer/
---
{% set persona = personas | findPersona(personaId) %}
<div class="site-main" data-persona="{{ persona.id }}">
  <div style="border-left:3px solid {{ persona.color }};padding-left:16px;margin-bottom:2em;">
    <div style="font-size:10px;letter-spacing:1.8px;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:6px;">Path</div>
    <h1>{{ persona.name }}</h1>
    <p style="color:var(--text2);">{{ persona.couplet[0] }} {{ persona.couplet[1] }}</p>
  </div>

  <p style="color:var(--text2);max-width:640px;line-height:1.7;">
    You've got the QB2 running. Now you want to personalize it, push it, break it just enough to understand what's inside. This track is the playground. LED scripts that respond to chip temperature. tt-toplike demos that stop conversations cold. An Ubuntu setup that actually fits your workflow. A recovery playbook for when experimentation goes sideways. And the community that makes all of it more interesting than any single machine ever could be on its own.
  </p>

  <div style="margin-top:2em;">
    {% for ch in persona.chapters %}
    <a href="/tinkerer/{{ ch.slug }}/" style="display:flex;align-items:baseline;gap:12px;padding:14px 0;border-bottom:1px solid var(--bg1);text-decoration:none;color:inherit;">
      <span style="color:{{ persona.color }};font-weight:700;font-size:13px;min-width:20px;font-variant-numeric:tabular-nums;">{{ loop.index }}</span>
      <span style="color:var(--text);font-weight:500;">{{ ch.title }}</span>
      <span style="margin-left:auto;font-size:11px;color:var(--muted);white-space:nowrap;">{{ ch.time }} min</span>
    </a>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>

  <div style="margin-top:2.5em;padding:16px;background:var(--bg1);border-radius:8px;border-left:3px solid var(--teal);">
    <div style="font-size:11px;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:6px;letter-spacing:0.5px;">New to QB2?</div>
    <a href="/first-timer/" style="color:var(--teal);font-size:13px;font-weight:500;">Take the First Timer track first — it covers hardware, boot, and your first model →</a>
  </div>
</div>
